POLICE DEPARTMENT - BALTIMORE, MARYLAND
INDIVIDUAL OVERTIME REPORT

06:36.186 --> 06:37.397
MONDAY

06:47.322 --> 06:48.949
Where there's smoke, there's fire.

06:49.784 --> 06:53.119
These officers, they're 1930s-style
gangsters.

06:53.621 --> 06:57.165
WE OWN THIS CITY

07:02.422 --> 07:06.050
Detective Gondo,
you joined the GTTF 2010.

07:06.509 --> 07:07.717
Two years before Rayam.

07:08.344 --> 07:10.221
He got bounced around
for a couple of years.

07:10.304 --> 07:12.765
He was battling
an Internal Affairs investigation.

07:13.181 --> 07:17.561
Before Rayam joined the GTTF,
what was going on within the squad?

07:18.771 --> 07:22.983
Nothing inappropriate.
Nothing criminal. Not really.

07:23.817 --> 07:26.736
And then after he came back
from his suspension and rejoined?

07:28.321 --> 07:29.991
I mean, this shit
just seemed to go downhill.

07:35.580 --> 07:36.831
That's all for now.

07:48.217 --> 07:49.469
All right, man, come on.

07:55.725 --> 07:59.728
Gondo doesn't have a problem
talking about a guy he says was his boy.

08:00.146 --> 08:01.272
Some friend.

08:02.356 --> 08:05.818
Man, it's hard to believe
Rayam has all those shootings,

08:05.902 --> 08:09.405
lies to the investigators,
gets caught on those lies, and...

08:10.405 --> 08:13.033
and when he comes off suspension,
they reward him

08:13.117 --> 08:15.702
by dropping him
in one of the most elite squads

08:15.786 --> 08:16.913
in the BPD.

08:18.539 --> 08:19.998
Cream rises to the top.

08:23.336 --> 08:27.006
MAY 2016

08:27.088 --> 08:30.216
TWELVE MONTHS EARLIER

08:30.300 --> 08:34.055
Copy, turning 11 around.
Fifteen blocks away. Can I get a...

08:34.471 --> 08:35.430
No ID?

08:36.265 --> 08:37.350
Nothing on him.

08:38.558 --> 08:40.311
Rigor says he's been there a while.

08:42.104 --> 08:43.730
I'll start knocking on doors.

08:51.071 --> 08:52.031
You all right?

08:55.992 --> 08:58.538
Just a moment of your time. All right?
That's all I need.

09:04.502 --> 09:07.045
How you doin' today, sir?
Detective Sean Suiter.

09:08.088 --> 09:10.383
-You are?
-I'm not inclined to give my name.

09:11.466 --> 09:12.676
Do you live around here?

09:12.760 --> 09:14.679
I stay up on Bond, near Preston.

09:14.761 --> 09:17.514
I was wondering if you saw or heard
anything related to this,

09:17.889 --> 09:19.057
probably last night.

09:21.060 --> 09:22.727
By any chance,
do you recognize the victim?

09:22.811 --> 09:25.648
Look, let me be straight with you,
Detective, to save you some time.

09:26.566 --> 09:27.649
I don't talk to police.

09:28.024 --> 09:30.570
-I'm Homicide.
-Make no difference to me.

09:31.277 --> 09:32.822
Ain't nobody born Homicide.

09:33.655 --> 09:35.408
Were you one of those jump-out boys?

09:36.826 --> 09:38.618
I did that for a while, yes.

09:38.703 --> 09:42.206
Some of y'all rob people.
Hell, I got robbed my damn self.

09:43.874 --> 09:45.000
Look, nothing personal.

09:45.084 --> 09:47.295
But I've been living in Baltimore
all my life.

09:48.087 --> 09:50.338
I know. I know.

09:51.131 --> 09:52.091
Just a moment.

09:54.259 --> 09:58.138
Something comes to you... please call.

10:05.353 --> 10:08.149
Hey, Sean. These houses are vacant here.

10:08.606 --> 10:09.858
So what else we got, Charlie?

10:09.942 --> 10:10.985
What do you want?

10:11.067 --> 10:13.195
I got Fourth Amendment violations,
warrantless searches...

10:13.278 --> 10:15.488
You know what people are gonna say
out in the suburbs?

10:15.573 --> 10:18.491
Hell, you know what half the country
would say if they were to read this stuff?

10:19.327 --> 10:22.330
"They might not have been guilty of
something on the day they got pulled over

10:22.412 --> 10:24.915
or jacked up, but they damn sure
were guilty of something."

10:25.458 --> 10:26.416
So?

10:26.958 --> 10:30.129
So I'm saying,
in the minds of Wonder Bread Americans,

10:30.211 --> 10:32.547
these people aren't really victims.
They deserved it.

10:33.549 --> 10:35.175
Ahmed's right about the optics.

10:35.592 --> 10:38.596
Look, we dug up instances
where Baltimore police came down on people

10:38.678 --> 10:40.723
who weren't drug dealers,
who weren't doing anything dirty.

10:41.098 --> 10:43.141
These folks had no previous charges
whatsoever

10:43.476 --> 10:46.144
outside of simple marijuana possession
or traffic violations.

10:46.562 --> 10:49.065
I've got claims that cops
flat-out robbed straight citizens.

10:49.857 --> 10:51.733
Hold on. Let's see...

10:53.568 --> 10:54.694
Here it is.

10:55.696 --> 10:58.157
Guy's name is James Otis.
You should talk to him.

10:58.239 --> 10:59.742
He ran afoul of a guy we know and love.

11:00.742 --> 11:04.580
Our old friend. All right.
I'll go and talk to him.

11:05.206 --> 11:08.041
We have a little time to add
the finishing touches to the decree.

11:17.926 --> 11:19.094
There's Gondo.

11:21.846 --> 11:24.432
Be advised,
the subject has gone to ground.

11:26.852 --> 11:29.145
We'll wait to be sure he's in
for the night, then move.

11:30.356 --> 11:31.315
Copy that.

11:41.491 --> 11:42.618
Okay.

11:42.700 --> 11:45.371
Hey, I can do this for you.

11:46.288 --> 11:47.581
You can do this for me?

11:48.164 --> 11:49.749
I mean, you know, in case...

11:50.584 --> 11:51.752
In case what?

11:51.835 --> 11:53.421
I'm just saying. You know,
I mean, it's dark,

11:53.503 --> 11:55.798
-you're crawling around in there.
-It's dark and I can't find my way

11:55.880 --> 11:57.799
around the interior of a Chevrolet?

12:00.927 --> 12:02.387
I guess that didn't sound right.

12:03.429 --> 12:04.890
How did you want it to sound?

12:04.973 --> 12:07.475
Like a middle-aged White guy from 1974.

12:07.559 --> 12:09.186
No, you pretty much nailed that.

12:10.562 --> 12:11.604
We are a go.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.649
Copy that. We see her on the move.

12:15.234 --> 12:16.734
Come on, come on, come on.

12:33.169 --> 12:34.460
Testing. Can you hear me?

12:40.509 --> 12:41.677
Okay.

12:41.759 --> 12:42.802
She's out.

12:42.886 --> 12:44.305
Copy. We hear it.

12:44.805 --> 12:47.182
Picked you up as soon as you got in.
Clear as a bell.

12:47.266 --> 12:49.977
Sound activated.
So as soon as you open that door,

12:50.059 --> 12:51.061
it kicked in.

12:52.062 --> 12:54.148
Okay, we're set. All clear.

12:54.772 --> 12:58.693
Oh, man. Oh, no.
I think I messed my hair up.

12:59.444 --> 13:02.364
-Oh, Johnny, how's my hair look?
-Okay. Enough. Thank you.

13:07.660 --> 13:11.831
No casings anywhere around the body.
Could be he got done with a revolver.

13:12.624 --> 13:14.209
Or the casings got picked up.

13:16.212 --> 13:17.212
Well...

13:19.380 --> 13:20.840
Autopsy will tell us tomorrow.

13:21.341 --> 13:23.260
We're not gonna get much help
from the residents.

13:25.095 --> 13:27.681
Man you spoke to earlier
was rough on you, huh?

13:28.349 --> 13:31.100
Well, he's right about some things.
He had his truth.

13:32.060 --> 13:34.063
I had my path. I took it to get here.

13:36.356 --> 13:37.398
I like what I'm doing now.

13:37.942 --> 13:40.444
I'm not gonna get all dramatic about it,
say it's my calling.

13:40.526 --> 13:45.073
But being in Homicide,
doing this kind of work, it feels right.

13:47.659 --> 13:50.746
But working drugs,
that wasn't my finest hour.

13:51.955 --> 13:55.500
I mean, that shit was pointless, really.

13:56.960 --> 13:58.546
And I saw some things.

14:09.807 --> 14:11.266
That was a long time ago.

14:16.229 --> 14:18.399
You want another? I'm buying.

14:19.525 --> 14:21.902
In that case, let me get something
off the top shelf.

14:41.297 --> 14:42.631
-James Otis?
-That's right.

14:42.714 --> 14:45.342
Nicole Steele, DOJ. Thank you.

14:49.053 --> 14:50.221
It's quiet in here.

14:50.556 --> 14:52.473
We got three kids, so that's unusual.

14:53.349 --> 14:55.936
Two of 'em are in school today.
And my wife took the youngest one out

14:56.020 --> 14:57.020
so we could talk.

14:58.313 --> 14:59.605
Are you currently employed?

15:00.273 --> 15:03.526
Not currently.
I was a HVAC repairman, you know,

15:03.611 --> 15:05.778
heating and air? I'll get to that.

15:06.572 --> 15:07.739
Tell me about the incident.

15:10.033 --> 15:11.535
You mean, when I got pulled over.

15:13.703 --> 15:15.873
I had just grabbed some pizza for me
and my family,

15:15.956 --> 15:17.833
at that Ledo's they got behind Hopkins.

15:22.504 --> 15:25.132
And I was headed home
on a street off of North Avenue,

15:25.965 --> 15:27.593
near Green Mount Cemetery.

15:29.344 --> 15:30.887
It was Hersl and two others.

15:30.971 --> 15:33.223
And this wasn't the first time
I got stopped by Officer Hersl.

15:33.682 --> 15:37.770
He had a thing about my car, I guess.
Anyway, they said my taillight was out.

15:38.102 --> 15:39.188
Was it?

15:39.270 --> 15:42.148
Yeah, it was. I got this classic car,

15:42.523 --> 15:44.567
an Impala SS. I bought on time.

15:44.984 --> 15:48.030
I knew my light was out,
but I was waiting on the bulb to come in.

15:48.488 --> 15:50.282
Not easy to get parts on older cars.

15:51.491 --> 15:54.036
Homer Avenue. Still in Lower Park Heights?

15:54.828 --> 15:56.079
That's a nice neighborhood.

15:56.163 --> 15:57.957
If you're gonna give me a citation
for that taillight,

15:58.039 --> 15:59.792
give me one.
I'm trying to get home to my family.

16:01.210 --> 16:04.003
Oh, you see that?
Assaulting a police officer. Cuff his ass.

16:04.338 --> 16:05.798
Motherfucker.

16:05.881 --> 16:06.881
What'd you say?

16:07.591 --> 16:12.137
Oh, shit. You know what? That reminds me,
I almost forgot to search your vehicle.

16:13.930 --> 16:15.515
Man, you got no cause for that.

16:15.598 --> 16:16.557
Yes, I do.

16:21.522 --> 16:24.482
Could it be that sweet, sickening smell?

16:24.566 --> 16:26.610
You know, the one they told us about
in middle school?

16:26.692 --> 16:28.696
Middle school about as far
as you got, too.

16:28.778 --> 16:31.073
-Yeah, keep talking.
-Sit down, asshole.

16:32.616 --> 16:33.741
Had you been smoking weed?

16:34.367 --> 16:36.954
I mean, everybody got that smell
on them these days.

16:37.454 --> 16:39.123
You catch it just walking down the street.

16:39.997 --> 16:42.583
Cops use that as an excuse
to toss your car all the time.

16:43.085 --> 16:44.168
Okay. What happened next?

16:44.628 --> 16:45.753
Hersl robbed me.

16:48.214 --> 16:50.925
I had just cashed my paycheck
at the M-and-T on Fayette.

16:52.928 --> 16:54.345
Six hundred and fifty-eight dollars.

16:56.806 --> 17:00.644
All right, come on. On your feet.
Let's go, up, up, up.

17:01.727 --> 17:04.856
You take my money?
You take my money, Hersl?

17:04.940 --> 17:06.275
You ain't right, man.

17:06.358 --> 17:07.818
-That's some bullshit.
-Get up there, let's go.

17:12.740 --> 17:15.450
I was jail side for two days
before anyone got to me.

17:16.325 --> 17:17.327
Otis.

17:21.164 --> 17:22.916
Never even spoke to a public defender.

17:23.416 --> 17:25.877
A state prosecutor they had there
interviewed me,

17:25.961 --> 17:28.922
and when I told him what happened,
he had me sign a form

17:29.005 --> 17:31.175
that waived my right
to sue the city for false arrest,

17:31.591 --> 17:34.051
in exchange for them throwing out
the charges on the spot.

17:34.760 --> 17:36.846
They knew what they had on me
was bullshit and wouldn't stick.

17:37.765 --> 17:40.057
So it never went to court.
That's a good thing, right?

17:40.142 --> 17:41.310
Let me finish.

17:41.392 --> 17:42.685
Come on, man. Give me a break.

17:42.770 --> 17:44.896
-On account of the days I was locked up...
-I got a family.

17:44.980 --> 17:47.316
...my calls went unserviced,
and we lost a couple customers.

17:47.398 --> 17:49.358
-Sorry, James.
-My employer told me he had to let me go.

17:49.443 --> 17:50.736
You had no recourse?

17:50.819 --> 17:52.905
I already signed away
my right to a lawsuit,

17:53.321 --> 17:54.363
I told you that.

17:54.907 --> 17:56.908
But I did file a complaint, on principle.

17:59.119 --> 18:00.496
Did you get your money back, at least?

18:01.705 --> 18:04.041
Shit. Of the 658 dollars he took?

18:04.666 --> 18:07.002
Hersl submitted 50 to Evidence Control.

18:08.419 --> 18:10.672
-He pocketed the rest.
-You surprised?

18:14.510 --> 18:16.010
He probably drank my money away.

18:21.140 --> 18:22.225
Hell yeah.

18:22.643 --> 18:25.521
-About to take all your money.
-Or had himself a good old time with it.

18:26.938 --> 18:27.980
Let's see what you got.

18:28.315 --> 18:29.273
Goddamn!

18:29.858 --> 18:31.151
Some shit like that.

18:31.235 --> 18:33.529
Come on. I'll spot ya, I'll spot ya.
Come on.

18:33.612 --> 18:34.571
It was nothing to him.

18:35.738 --> 18:36.740
-Later.
-You go ahead.

18:37.281 --> 18:39.576
That money meant something to me.
I earned it.

18:40.077 --> 18:42.621
My wife and me,
we got no cushion, for real.

18:43.329 --> 18:46.666
When I cash my paycheck,
every penny goes to my mortgage,

18:47.126 --> 18:49.043
groceries, stuff for my kids.

18:49.835 --> 18:52.755
This set me back.
Bank's about to repo my car.

18:53.506 --> 18:56.468
If I do get a job now,
how am I supposed to get to work?

18:57.511 --> 18:59.971
Everyone who lives here
knows what time it is.

19:00.054 --> 19:04.017
Police treating all of us like criminals,
people like me, my family.

19:13.694 --> 19:18.115
Detective Rayam, your partner, Gondo,
says that when you joined GTTF,

19:18.197 --> 19:21.367
things, in his words,
"Began to go downhill."

19:22.619 --> 19:24.787
Yo, Gondo was in the mix from the start.

19:24.872 --> 19:27.541
All right? It wasn't me who cultivated
a relationship with Brill.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.709
You mean, Antonio Shropshire.

19:30.042 --> 19:31.002
Right.

19:31.586 --> 19:34.798
That goes back to when they were kids,
long before Gondo knew me.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.843
And honestly, neither one of us
supervised the squad.

19:39.469 --> 19:40.636
We just followed the leader.

19:41.178 --> 19:42.555
You're talking about Wayne Jenkins?

19:43.014 --> 19:45.349
And Allers before him, too. Shit.

19:46.268 --> 19:47.476
Oh, fuck. You know...

19:48.477 --> 19:50.021
There was this...

19:51.856 --> 19:54.233
one robbery back in...

19:55.318 --> 19:56.569
2014.

19:57.279 --> 19:59.823
Allers got the tip from a CI
he'd been working with.

20:00.448 --> 20:02.910
Out in West Edmondale?

20:03.409 --> 20:07.080
That's it. Fifty-four-54.
One with the white bars on the door.

20:07.664 --> 20:09.791
Sergeant Allers brought his son
with us on that one.

20:10.333 --> 20:12.836
I reckon it was
a "Bring your Kid to Work Day."

20:14.003 --> 20:15.797
-Husband and wife team.
-Yes, sir.

20:16.256 --> 20:18.592
George Williams
and Yolanda Paige-Williams.

20:21.385 --> 20:23.971
G, this shit could be big, man.

20:24.056 --> 20:27.308
Yeah, seen his photo.
Bigger than a motherfucker.

20:28.351 --> 20:29.935
Are we gonna call
the county boys in on this?

20:30.478 --> 20:33.398
After we see what we got.
Come on, y'all ready to do this?

20:33.941 --> 20:35.234
-Let's go. You ready?
-Let's go, man.

20:35.317 --> 20:37.526
-Wake your ass us up, motherfucker.
-Let's go.

20:47.453 --> 20:48.996
All right, son, you fall back right here.

20:52.251 --> 20:53.668
-Police!
-What do you want?

20:54.253 --> 20:55.211
Police!

20:56.587 --> 20:58.089
-Stand back. Get down!
-Stand back, motherfucker.

20:58.548 --> 20:59.715
That house was hot.

21:00.634 --> 21:02.970
We cleaned the fuck up. Wife shit.

21:05.096 --> 21:07.973
Hey. Don't play with me.

21:12.645 --> 21:17.066
Seventy, 80, 90, 100.
Look at this shit, baby.

21:17.900 --> 21:19.527
That's a hundred grand right there.

21:19.611 --> 21:22.197
There was 416,000 dollars in that bedroom.

21:22.279 --> 21:25.199
-Forty, fifty, sixty, seventy...
-When the county police showed up,

21:25.284 --> 21:26.868
they found three-fifty.

21:27.202 --> 21:28.203
You believe this shit?

21:28.662 --> 21:31.790
-Shit. Stop playing with me.
-Detective Ward, when Wayne Jenkins

21:31.873 --> 21:35.334
took over the supervision
of the GTTF from Sergeant Allers,

21:36.669 --> 21:37.879
what was the biggest change?

21:39.131 --> 21:42.050
Well, I came after Allers,
but from what I heard,

21:42.675 --> 21:44.386
it wasn't like he didn't know
how to steal.

21:44.468 --> 21:48.180
It was just Jenks, man,
he... he was something else.

21:48.265 --> 21:49.223
Tell us.

21:51.393 --> 21:54.186
Well, you gotta remember,
it was like a new squad.

21:54.813 --> 21:57.983
Me, Taylor, Hendrix, and Jenkins
had just come on.

21:58.065 --> 22:02.070
And later on, Jenkins added this new kid,
Kost-o-please.

22:03.028 --> 22:04.613
James Kostoplis.

22:04.698 --> 22:05.656
K-Stop.

22:06.533 --> 22:09.619
Yeah, his people are
from one of them countries over there.

22:10.870 --> 22:13.498
But Jenkins knew him
from when he was a patrol sergeant

22:13.582 --> 22:15.750
in the Northeast.
K-Stop was in his squad over there.

22:17.961 --> 22:21.882
I make big money, I drive big cars
Everybody know me

22:21.965 --> 22:25.344
This kid adored Jenkins.
I mean, he really looked up to him.

22:25.926 --> 22:28.262
I feel I'm being tailed
By the same sucker's head lights

22:30.931 --> 22:34.852
And also when he came,
Jenkins told us new guys

22:34.936 --> 22:37.230
that Gondo and Rayam
were under federal investigation

22:37.314 --> 22:38.357
for selling drugs.

22:38.939 --> 22:41.651
Were Gondo and Rayam...
Did they seem concerned?

22:43.152 --> 22:44.863
Not really. I mean,

22:45.196 --> 22:47.823
when Jenks came in, everybody was excited
about the money.

22:48.407 --> 22:49.450
To be honest with you,

22:49.534 --> 22:51.119
nobody really thought too hard
on anything else.

22:51.202 --> 22:52.162
The money?

22:52.662 --> 22:53.621
The overtime pay.

22:55.290 --> 22:57.500
With Jenkins,
it was like we had permission

22:57.584 --> 22:58.584
to rob that fund.

22:58.960 --> 23:01.004
The faucet was on, full force.

23:02.589 --> 23:05.133
I don't know Jenkins. Not like you.

23:05.675 --> 23:07.260
All right.
Let me tell you how this boy be.

23:08.553 --> 23:12.182
He'll come in late every day.
So we don't come in till 10:00, 11:00.

23:13.349 --> 23:16.477
And depending on how he feel,
we might roll out on regular time.

23:17.729 --> 23:20.357
That's how he gets down, man.
We got that green light.

23:20.689 --> 23:24.610
Some supervisor told Jenks
the overtime budget is wide open.

23:25.195 --> 23:26.946
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-"Work as much as you want."

23:28.739 --> 23:29.699
Bet.

23:30.616 --> 23:33.787
Ain't no thing, man. You gonna like him,
you gonna like Jenks. Matter of fact...

23:35.997 --> 23:38.874
last night, Jenkins tells us
to put in slips

23:39.584 --> 23:42.837
for six OT hours.
We ain't even work a full shift.

23:43.755 --> 23:46.006
Then we banging... We like this.
Banging that OT, G.

23:46.091 --> 23:47.884
-Hey. Yeah, hit me with that.
-You know what I'm saying?

23:48.259 --> 23:49.844
-He cool.
-I'm with that.

23:51.136 --> 23:52.597
-Yeah.
-He crazy, but he cool.

23:53.598 --> 23:55.850
The summary reads like butter.

23:59.438 --> 24:00.480
Got it all done.

24:00.897 --> 24:03.358
Mayor Rawlings-Blake asked for it.
And she'll get her copy

24:03.440 --> 24:05.068
just in time for her to make her exit.

24:05.944 --> 24:09.072
"The Baltimore Police Department
engages in a practice

24:09.154 --> 24:11.532
or pattern of making
unconstitutional stops, searches,

24:11.616 --> 24:12.575
and arrests."

24:13.410 --> 24:15.579
Here we go. "Disparities in
the rates of stops,

24:15.661 --> 24:17.330
searches, and arrests
of African Americans,"

24:17.414 --> 24:20.374
and, "Driven by systemic deficiencies
of BPD policies, training,

24:20.459 --> 24:22.418
supervision,
and accountability structures."

24:22.501 --> 24:24.129
This is incendiary shit.

24:24.212 --> 24:26.298
I would hope so. But it's not a directive.

24:26.380 --> 24:28.257
We still have to get
the consent decree signed.

24:28.341 --> 24:29.550
-Right.
-So we drop that on Pugh

24:29.634 --> 24:32.386
-as soon as she puts on the crown.
-We moving pretty fast now.

24:32.471 --> 24:33.929
We gotta get the consent decree out there

24:34.014 --> 24:35.723
before the new administration comes in,
in January.

24:36.099 --> 24:37.434
Hilary's AG, whoever that is,

24:37.517 --> 24:39.643
should be a little bit sympathetic
to police reform.

24:40.728 --> 24:41.688
Assuming...

24:42.189 --> 24:43.773
How is your friend,
the police commissioner,

24:43.856 --> 24:44.940
gonna like this?

24:56.536 --> 24:57.620
Have you read this?

24:57.703 --> 24:59.496
-I read enough.
-We're doing our jobs.

24:59.581 --> 25:01.540
What do people want,
for us to stop policing?

25:02.124 --> 25:05.378
They want us to do it in a better way,
without the collateral damage.

25:05.461 --> 25:07.504
But how? How do you keep control
with this much violence

25:07.588 --> 25:08.547
without being aggressive?

25:09.841 --> 25:12.217
It doesn't help that shit like this
gets everyone all ginned up.

25:14.513 --> 25:17.807
These popped up all over the city.
Idiots misspelled "loiterers".

25:18.515 --> 25:19.600
It does make a point.

25:23.437 --> 25:24.439
Is that all?

25:31.320 --> 25:32.948
Hey, G, what up? What up?

25:33.031 --> 25:35.534
Look, Jemell, I know
Jenkins do some crazy shit.

25:35.617 --> 25:38.786
You don't gotta tell me.
You know, Jenks is code-motherfucking-red.

25:38.869 --> 25:42.916
All right, but look, this last paycheck
I just got from the city?

25:44.083 --> 25:46.126
Eight thousand dollars.

25:46.211 --> 25:49.464
When I looked at it, I was like,
"Oh, my God, who did this?"

25:50.339 --> 25:51.298
"This is a lie."

25:52.633 --> 25:56.303
Telling you, there's a method
to Jenkins' madness. He...

25:56.638 --> 25:59.139
Yeah. Yeah, that motherfucker
off the chain, G.

25:59.682 --> 26:00.892
Look, like I said,

26:01.351 --> 26:04.020
let's go at this shit hard.
Let's enjoy this shit while we can

26:04.103 --> 26:05.980
'cause all good things come to an end.

26:06.064 --> 26:07.065
For real.

26:07.815 --> 26:10.693
But Jenks,
man, he off the fucking chain, yo.

26:11.485 --> 26:13.487
He off the motherfucking chain, B.

26:13.570 --> 26:15.030
He off the fucking chain, B.

26:15.114 --> 26:17.116
I swear, that nigga off the chain, G.

26:19.869 --> 26:23.873
All this bogus overtime they're banking,
we'll get every one of 'em on wire fraud.

26:23.956 --> 26:26.126
Bring in the IRS
and we got tax evasion too.

26:26.209 --> 26:27.419
The old-fashioned way.

26:27.502 --> 26:29.254
I'm starting to love me
some Wayne Jenkins.

26:29.337 --> 26:30.547
He off the chain, yo.

26:33.841 --> 26:36.760
I read most of your book, Mr. Grabler.

26:36.845 --> 26:39.764
And sure enough,
you write about many of the same issues

26:39.847 --> 26:42.267
that we at the DOJ are trying to address.

26:42.350 --> 26:43.517
Thank you.

26:43.602 --> 26:47.438
You know, there's an old joke
that inside of every old cop is a book.

26:48.147 --> 26:50.150
And that's exactly where it should stay.

26:50.859 --> 26:53.110
Well, you certainly wrote from experience.

26:53.193 --> 26:55.572
Oh, I did. I did. I came on in '72.

26:57.198 --> 27:00.243
Walking foot up in the Northwest,
and then...

27:00.743 --> 27:05.372
plainclothes ops, after that, narcotics.
And I did my longest stint in Homicide.

27:05.706 --> 27:08.542
After my retirement, I ended up back here,
at the Academy, teaching.

27:08.627 --> 27:10.253
Sounds like a rewarding career.

27:10.335 --> 27:14.506
It was, it was.
I loved being a cop, you know.

27:14.591 --> 27:16.800
I loved it when the job meant something,
when you could...

27:17.552 --> 27:20.138
make an arrest for a street robbery,
or a rapist,

27:20.220 --> 27:22.347
or put down a murderer.
There was nothing finer.

27:22.724 --> 27:25.434
Nothing finer.
But people had to talk to you,

27:25.517 --> 27:27.103
and once upon a time, they did.

27:27.729 --> 27:31.231
Well, of course, not all of them.
There is a street code for snitching.

27:31.316 --> 27:32.901
But there were always

27:32.983 --> 27:35.402
enough people on the post
that would talk to you.

27:35.487 --> 27:36.987
That trust is broken.

27:37.072 --> 27:39.323
Yeah, well, you can't...
you can't get information out of somebody

27:39.407 --> 27:41.701
while you're beating on 'em,
or you got your hand in their pocket.

27:41.785 --> 27:44.162
-And then lying about it in court.
-Yeah.

27:44.953 --> 27:49.000
You know... everything changed
when they came up with that expression,

27:49.084 --> 27:50.751
"The War on Drugs."

27:51.543 --> 27:53.713
What an idiotic fucking thing to say.

27:54.589 --> 27:56.883
What the hell is a war on drugs?
What does that mean?

27:57.342 --> 27:59.761
Waging a war against citizens...

28:00.677 --> 28:03.555
by definition is separating us
into two opposing camps.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.641
The colonizer and the colonized.

28:06.433 --> 28:08.227
Albert Memmi, very good. Yes.

28:08.769 --> 28:10.897
And with the war
comes police militarization.

28:11.313 --> 28:14.191
SWAT teams, tactical squads,
stop-and-frisk,

28:14.525 --> 28:17.696
strip searches, a complete gutting
of the Fourth Amendment.

28:18.530 --> 28:21.700
And it's like we're, we're fighting
terrorists on foreign soil.

28:22.032 --> 28:24.868
And you can't just blame the cops.
We serve the politicians,

28:24.952 --> 28:28.789
who thrive on being tough on crime.

28:28.873 --> 28:30.041
Zero tolerance.

28:30.124 --> 28:34.503
Zero tolerance, quality of life arrests.
Having a beer on your own stoop.

28:35.045 --> 28:38.757
Loitering, spitting on the sidewalk,
existing.

28:39.800 --> 28:40.759
Existing.

28:42.512 --> 28:46.349
In 2005, I think it was,
when O'Malley was still mayor,

28:46.849 --> 28:51.896
they made 100,000 arrests,
most of them Black, most of them poor.

28:51.979 --> 28:56.733
That's almost one arrest
for every six Baltimoreans in one year.

28:56.818 --> 29:00.280
They jacked up people six, seven times,
maybe 12 times.

29:00.362 --> 29:03.825
And many of those arrests were illegal,
never made it to court.

29:04.199 --> 29:05.744
But they got their stats.

29:08.580 --> 29:09.705
What do you teach here?

29:10.747 --> 29:11.958
I teach the law

29:12.624 --> 29:14.586
to cadets who are
about to hit the streets.

29:14.668 --> 29:16.671
Fourth, Fifth, and Sixth Amendments.

29:17.296 --> 29:19.758
A cop can't uphold the law
unless he understands the law.

29:20.800 --> 29:23.678
I teach these young kids to be good,
honest cops.

29:25.095 --> 29:26.306
The rest is up to them.

29:27.222 --> 29:29.057
You've given a lot of thought to this.

29:29.600 --> 29:30.601
Yeah.

29:32.061 --> 29:33.897
I come off as angry sometimes.

29:36.232 --> 29:37.399
Aren't you angry?

29:43.948 --> 29:46.450
So at some point, Jenkins told you
that you were under investigation?

29:47.492 --> 29:50.454
We knew. By that time...

29:51.163 --> 29:52.748
we had a sense y'all was on us.

29:53.625 --> 29:56.211
There wasn't no charade about the fact
Jenkins was in the shit, too.

29:57.629 --> 30:00.005
There was this one night
where we pulled over a suspect,

30:00.505 --> 30:01.966
then followed him to his house.

30:02.842 --> 30:05.178
Took him off
for like a pound of marijuana to sell.

30:06.011 --> 30:07.304
Jenkins told me to off it.

30:08.556 --> 30:09.681
Did you?

30:09.766 --> 30:12.517
No. I had Gondo sell it
through his friend, Glen Wells.

30:13.018 --> 30:15.021
Yeah, but you must have had
your own connect

30:15.103 --> 30:17.231
to sell the drugs
that you've been confiscating.

30:17.315 --> 30:19.066
That was my boy up in Philadelphia.

30:19.150 --> 30:20.317
Let's come back to that.

30:20.400 --> 30:24.614
On July 15 of 2016, you and other GTTF,

30:25.156 --> 30:28.158
detained a Ronald and Nancy Hamilton.

30:30.203 --> 30:32.579
Oh, shit. Y'all remember that?

30:33.413 --> 30:35.249
The f... That's fuckin' impressive.

30:35.333 --> 30:37.626
We have you and Gondo on tape,
discussing it.

30:39.169 --> 30:40.338
Right.

30:40.420 --> 30:44.801
Well, yeah, we got the tip on Hamilton
from a sergeant in the Southwestern.

30:45.260 --> 30:47.679
We got a warrant from a judge.
I put a tracker on the car.

30:48.179 --> 30:50.431
He had a big old house out
in Carroll County with a pool.

30:50.515 --> 30:52.892
Motherfucker was a monster. Shit.

30:52.975 --> 30:54.268
You had authority for the tracker?

30:54.352 --> 30:56.229
Hell, no. Did that on my own.

30:56.812 --> 30:59.107
Anyway, after we decided to do,
you know, the thing,

30:59.481 --> 31:01.985
we followed the Hamiltons
to Reisterstown Road.

31:02.067 --> 31:03.570
-Where's your money at, Hoss?
-Jacked 'em up.

31:03.652 --> 31:04.779
Let's see what you got here.

31:04.863 --> 31:07.322
Is that a cellphone?
Now, where that money at?

31:08.408 --> 31:10.535
I found a roll of cash on Hamilton
right there.

31:10.618 --> 31:13.036
Put your hands down. Go over there.
Yo, go over there.

31:13.121 --> 31:15.664
Shit had to be drug money,
so I knew we had the right dude.

31:15.748 --> 31:16.915
Don't talk to her.

31:16.999 --> 31:18.167
Sergeant Jenkins there?

31:18.250 --> 31:20.085
No. He was at the barn.

31:20.877 --> 31:22.629
You see, the plan was to bring them there,

31:22.963 --> 31:25.133
and then to introduce Jenks
as a US Attorney.

31:27.134 --> 31:30.638
Oh, shit, fucking Jenkins
as a US Attorney.

31:31.013 --> 31:34.601
Oh, no offense intended there.

31:36.686 --> 31:40.105
Sir, I can see from your file here
that you are a smart individual

31:40.188 --> 31:41.858
and as a federal prosecutor,

31:41.940 --> 31:44.776
I have been dealing
with these kinda cases for quite a while,

31:45.360 --> 31:46.988
I'm just gonna tell you, full candor,

31:47.071 --> 31:49.573
Mr. Hamilton, you are looking
at a serious amount of years

31:49.657 --> 31:51.408
unless you start giving us
the right answers.

31:51.908 --> 31:54.453
Now, look, we have you
on three separate controlled buys.

31:54.536 --> 31:56.372
-Now, we...
-Man, get the fuck out of here.

31:56.456 --> 31:59.792
Okay, first off, I'm not "man," okay?
So, let's just do that again.

32:00.167 --> 32:03.713
-I'm a US Attorney, okay?
-Whatever. And I don't sell no drugs.

32:04.255 --> 32:05.380
Man, what are you doing?

32:06.591 --> 32:08.426
You have
multiple federal drug convictions.

32:08.508 --> 32:10.470
You did six years
because of those convictions.

32:10.553 --> 32:11.596
This says that right there.

32:11.678 --> 32:13.805
What do you think you gonna do?
You think you gonna outsmart me?

32:13.890 --> 32:15.349
Now, let's try this shit again.

32:15.934 --> 32:18.685
You currently own this home in...
in Westminster, correct?

32:19.854 --> 32:22.147
Do you currently have quantities of drugs
at that home?

32:28.070 --> 32:30.573
-Man, he don't like talking much, huh?
-No.

32:30.655 --> 32:32.574
I'm sorry, you're... you're hearing
what I'm saying, right?

32:32.659 --> 32:35.452
-I'm hearing you perfectly fucking clear.
-Am I not talking loud enough? What is it?

32:35.536 --> 32:36.788
You want me to be slower?

32:36.871 --> 32:39.248
-What is it? Is it... is it pronunciation?
-No, I heard you just fine.

32:39.331 --> 32:41.458
-What do you fuckin' think the deal is?
-Yeah. I heard you good.

32:41.542 --> 32:45.713
Do you currently have quantities of drugs
at your home in Westminster?

32:51.386 --> 32:54.679
Well, shit. Guess we're just gonna
have to go out there and find out.

32:57.642 --> 32:59.393
Hamilton's house was nice.

33:04.190 --> 33:05.690
Boom! Yahtzee.

33:06.234 --> 33:07.902
Hey, yo!

33:08.819 --> 33:09.778
I see money.

33:10.238 --> 33:11.655
-Come on.
-Bump that shit.

33:11.739 --> 33:13.490
-Hersl and Gondo found money.
-Into it.

33:13.949 --> 33:16.326
-But no drugs.
-Look at that. All right, man.

33:16.411 --> 33:17.869
-Yep!
-Hell, yeah!

33:17.953 --> 33:21.081
He left Hersl in the room,
which was a mistake.

33:21.748 --> 33:24.876
We were downstairs,
waiting on the State Police to arrive.

33:25.460 --> 33:28.131
Fifty K. Where the rest of it at?

33:30.591 --> 33:31.716
How you gonna take my money?

33:32.343 --> 33:34.886
I earned that gambling,
selling cars I get at auctions.

33:34.971 --> 33:36.597
We're seizing this under forfeiture laws.

33:36.680 --> 33:38.432
You'll have a chance
to account for it later.

33:38.515 --> 33:39.558
That's some bullshit.

33:40.308 --> 33:42.978
Appreciate it, fellas.
You all get home safe, all right?

33:44.271 --> 33:45.230
You left after that?

33:47.525 --> 33:48.568
Jenkins wasn't done.

33:49.901 --> 33:51.654
Man, this a nice ass crib, man.

33:52.905 --> 33:57.784
I tell you. Is that what you call it?
It's your crib, hmm?

33:58.827 --> 34:03.290
Goddamn. This was a long-ass drive, man,
so we gonna need something.

34:05.710 --> 34:07.295
Come on, man. Where the drugs at, man?

34:08.796 --> 34:10.046
What, you got one of those safes?

34:10.131 --> 34:12.759
-Ain't no fucking drugs.
-Okay, but you do know people, right?

34:13.509 --> 34:15.386
You know drug dealers.
Where's your plug, man?

34:15.469 --> 34:17.554
I know you know somebody.
Give us a name, baby.

34:18.723 --> 34:20.140
Look, here's the bottom line.

34:20.558 --> 34:22.767
You take care of us,
we're gonna take care of you,

34:22.851 --> 34:26.814
'cause here's the crazy part...
One morning, you could wake up

34:27.814 --> 34:29.484
with ten kilos in the backyard.

34:32.528 --> 34:34.113
You split up the Hamilton money?

34:34.571 --> 34:36.615
Yeah, later that night at a bar.

34:38.241 --> 34:41.412
When Gondo went back to the bedroom
for the cash, there was the 50,

34:42.120 --> 34:45.625
then there was the loose 20,000.
I mean, I had counted more.

34:46.084 --> 34:50.088
You know, Hersl must have taken
a few thousand when he was up there alone.

34:51.047 --> 34:54.217
Of course, I lifted the 3,500
off of Hamilton when we pulled him over.

34:54.299 --> 34:58.053
That... What I'm sayin' is,
we weren't just stealing, all right?

34:58.512 --> 34:59.722
We were stealing from each other.

35:01.640 --> 35:04.852
Jenkins more than most, though.
At that point in time,

35:05.852 --> 35:07.814
we was all in it for ourselves,
to be honest.

35:08.647 --> 35:12.693
But all this while you knew
we were looking at you.

