52:24.348 --> 52:25.432
Got it.

52:25.516 --> 52:28.311
But I... I made a wrong turn for a while.

52:28.395 --> 52:29.479
How so?

52:29.562 --> 52:33.066
Well, early on, I was
a Trial Team AUSA in DC,

52:33.150 --> 52:35.026
prosecuting mostly drug cases.

52:36.069 --> 52:38.155
And it got to me.

52:39.406 --> 52:42.616
Day in, day out, in courtrooms,
sending young Black men to prison.

52:44.411 --> 52:47.080
But I guess, I needed to go through that
to make the next step,

52:47.164 --> 52:48.248
and pivot to Civil Rights, so...

52:48.831 --> 52:50.040
You grew up in D.C.?

52:50.125 --> 52:55.046
Outside the city.
Bethesda. It's high-income, mostly White.

52:55.129 --> 52:58.508
You know, not a very diverse area
to say the least.

53:00.218 --> 53:04.306
My parents knew we'd lose
a little something growing up there,

53:04.389 --> 53:06.892
but they figured the benefits
outweighed the bad,

53:06.975 --> 53:08.393
and they were right.

53:09.351 --> 53:10.936
I have been very fortunate.

53:12.271 --> 53:17.109
You know, my kid brother,
he got a... a lot worse than I ever did.

53:18.152 --> 53:19.362
He's a tile man.

53:19.446 --> 53:21.406
He does high-end bathrooms.
A real craftsman.

53:21.864 --> 53:24.659
So, you know, he has his hair braided.
He wears workman's clothes,

53:24.743 --> 53:25.868
jeans, hoodies.

53:25.951 --> 53:29.289
When he was in his teens,
he'd be standing outside our house,

53:29.372 --> 53:33.792
and this happened more than once,
the Montgomery County Police would stop

53:33.876 --> 53:35.836
and ask him, "What are you doing here?"

53:36.920 --> 53:39.381
He'd point back at the house
that we grew up in,

53:39.465 --> 53:40.800
and he'd say, "I live here."

53:43.303 --> 53:44.720
They couldn't see a Bethesda kid.

53:46.640 --> 53:49.184
When they looked at James,
all they could see was a nigger.

53:53.103 --> 53:55.482
Yeah. Yeah, I get that.

53:55.564 --> 53:58.652
One time, he was coming home from work,
driving down our street,

53:59.318 --> 54:02.072
and a couple cop cars followed him
into our driveway.

54:03.281 --> 54:06.700
When James got out of the car,
I don't know, maybe he got out too fast,

54:06.785 --> 54:08.202
but they cuffed him.

54:08.744 --> 54:10.538
Said that he made a threatening move.

54:10.622 --> 54:13.457
And on the report, to justify the stop,
they lied.

54:13.541 --> 54:15.584
They said that he was speeding
down our street.

54:16.043 --> 54:18.671
All he was saying was,
"Why are you doing me like this?

54:19.506 --> 54:22.509
I just worked a 12-hour day,
and all I was doing

54:22.592 --> 54:24.177
was driving to my house."

54:25.886 --> 54:28.013
I came outside, and so did my father.

54:28.848 --> 54:31.684
And there was a Black cop,
and he wouldn't answer

54:31.768 --> 54:34.645
any of our questions.
And the other cop, the one who cuffed him,

54:34.728 --> 54:35.939
the White dude,

54:37.190 --> 54:38.191
he threatened my dad.

54:39.525 --> 54:42.569
And it was all for nothing.
None of the cops showed up in court.

54:45.031 --> 54:46.323
The damage was done.

54:48.867 --> 54:50.078
Where's your brother now?

54:51.121 --> 54:54.791
After that last incident,
he moved to Atlanta.

54:57.251 --> 54:58.503
I don't hate the police,

54:58.878 --> 55:02.090
but it's fair to say that my brother
has no love for them at all,

55:02.840 --> 55:04.134
and never will.

55:07.846 --> 55:10.639
I don't know if what we're doing
is gonna change a thing, Ahmed.

55:10.723 --> 55:11.724
But shit...

55:18.480 --> 55:19.481
You ready for another?

55:20.984 --> 55:23.528
I gotta go home. We have work to do.
